4. Projects

List these as cards. Each has a short line for the card and a longer blurb for a detail view or hover. Lead with oushi.

oushi — Personal AI assistant

Card line: An AI assistant that lives on top of your email and calendar, and reaches out to you.

Full blurb: A personal AI assistant built over Gmail and Google Calendar. It reads and triages email in real time through Gmail's Pub/Sub push notifications, understands sender and thread context, and proactively reaches out instead of waiting to be asked. Full auth, push notifications, and a clean daily-brief interface. Built and deployed end to end.

Stack: Next.js · TypeScript · Supabase · Google APIs (Gmail, Calendar) · Pub/Sub · Vercel

Links: Live demo · GitHub

What to highlight if asked: the real-time email pipeline (Pub/Sub over polling) and the proactive-outreach design. This is your strongest engineering story.


bluprint — AI career planning for students

Card line: Upload your CV, get an AI-generated career roadmap, resume analysis, and job-fit feedback.

Full blurb: A full-stack platform that turns a student's CV into a personalized career plan. It extracts a structured profile from an uploaded resume, generates a roadmap, analyzes the resume against job descriptions, and includes an assistant chat with saved history. End-to-end AI workflow from upload to actionable output.

Stack: Next.js · TypeScript · Tailwind · Supabase · Prisma · Google Gemini

Links: Live demo (bluprint1.vercel.app) · GitHub


YQuantum 2026 — Quantum portfolio optimization

Card line: Insurance portfolio selection solved on QuEra's neutral-atom quantum stack. Capgemini × The Hartford hackathon.

Full blurb: Built for the YQuantum 2026 challenge with Capgemini and The Hartford. Reduces a real investment dataset to an 8-qubit portfolio problem, computes the exact classical optimum as ground truth, then trains QAOA on QuEra's Bloqade stack to recover it. Includes penalty calibration so the soft-constrained problem provably preserves the hard-budget solution. Reached ~10.5% probability mass on the exact optimum at p=3.

Stack: Python · Bloqade · PyQrack · QAOA · QUBO

Links: GitHub

What to highlight: this is your depth/fundamentals project. It shows you can do real scientific computing, not just app-building.


Optical inspection stage — In progress

Card line: A 2-axis precision gantry with computer-vision defect detection and automated inspection reports.

Full blurb: A self-directed project merging hardware and software: a 2-axis gantry inspection stage paired with a YOLO-based computer-vision pipeline that detects and localizes defects, then generates structured inspection reports. Designed around real semiconductor-inspection workflows.

Stack: Python · YOLO · OpenCV · CAD (Creo) · FEA (Ansys)

